Description:
    This generator will create additional files that may be needed when working with a module in vets-api
	e.g. Controllers, Models, Serializers and Service Classes
	
	Important: If you try to create a component for a module that does not currently exist,
	you will be prompted via the command line with the choice to create the module.
	

Example:
    rails generate module_component foo method:controller

    This will create:
	modules/foo/app/controllers/foo/v0/foo_controller.rb

Example:
    rails generate module_component foo method:controller component_name:bar

    This will create:
	modules/foo/app/controllers/foo/v0/bar_controller.rb
		
Example:
    rails generate module_component foo method:model

    This will create:
	modules/foo/app/models/foo/v0/foo.rb

Example:
    rails generate module_component foo method:model component_name:bar

    This will create:
	modules/foo/app/models/foo/v0/bar.rb
		
Example:
    rails generate module_component foo method:serializer

    This will create:
	modules/foo/app/serializers/foo/v0/foo_serializer.rb

Example:
    rails generate module_component foo method:serializer component_name:bar

    This will create:
	modules/foo/app/serializers/foo/v0/bar_serializer.rb

Example:
    rails generate module_component foo method:service

    This will create:
	modules/foo/app/services/foo/v0/foo_service.rb	
	modules/foo/app/services/foo/v0/configuration.rb

Example:
    rails generate module_component foo method:service component_name:bar

    This will create:
	modules/foo/app/services/foo/v0/bar_service.rb	
	modules/foo/app/services/foo/v0/configuration.rb
